annotationA: Xylosyltransferase oxt; Catalyzes the first step in biosynthesis of glycosaminoglycan. Transfers D-xylose from UDP-D-xylose to specific serine residues of the core protein. Initial enzyme in the biosynthesis of chondroitin sulfate and dermatan sulfate proteoglycans in fibroblasts and chondrocytes; Belongs to the glycosyltransferase 14 family. XylT subfamily
annotationB: Hexosyltransferase; Galactosyltransferase II is involved in the synthesis of a common linkage tetrasaccharide structure of heparan (HS) and chondroitin sulfates (CS). Its roles include regulation of several signaling pathways (Hh, Dpp, Wingless) mediated by HS and CS in development
